  "market_context": "Recent bearish price action with two equal lows forming sell-side liquidity at 182700; price had been declining and testing this support zone repeatedly before the sweep.",
  "key_observation": "A single candle closed below the equal lows at 182700 (sell-side liquidity), then immediately reversed upward, while RSI showed a bullish divergence (price lower low, RSI higher low).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified two equal lows at 182700 on the GBPJPY 1H chart, labeling it as sell-side liquidity where longs defend and shorts expect breakout.",
    "Step 2: Observed a single candle that closed below the 182700 level, constituting a valid liquidity sweep pattern.",
    "Step 3: Noted that price immediately returned into the prior range after the sweep candle closed, indicating trap of bears and potential reversal.",
    "Step 4: Checked RSI indicator and confirmed bullish divergence: price made a lower low while RSI made a higher low, reinforcing reversal signal.",
    "Step 5: Concluded smart money likely went long after the sweep to engage buyside liquidity above."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Liquidity sweeps below equal lows can signal reversals when price returns quickly; RSI divergence adds high-probability confirmation—do not trade the break alone without reversal evidence.",
